data.description:
A corner lot property with a fenced in, spacious back yard. The kitchen has a new glass top stove, refrigerator, and dishwasher. The master bath has a double-vanity with a stand-up shower. There are 2 bedrooms upstairs, with a large landing area that can serve as a play area for kids or sitting lounge for adults. The house is about 20 minutes away from Duke Field, 30 minutes from Eglin, and 45 minutes from Hurlburt Field. There are many restaurant options within minutes and a large park across Hwy 90 with 2 ponds and a dog park. The neighborhood is quiet and tranquil, with many military families occupying the houses throughout the neighborhood. Military members can receive a reduced security deposit. No smoking and no pets.

No smoking and no pets allowed. The first month's rent and security deposit are due at the time of signing the lease agreement. The lease length will be 12 months, will the option to extend for 6 months or 12 months. The renter will be responsible for having all utilities in their name and paying for all utilities. Lawn maintenance is included in the HOA fees paid by the homeowner, so no yard maintenance is required by the tenant. Military members can receive a reduced security deposit rate by providing contact information for their chain of command and unit information.
